            "questionText": "A medical ultrasound device emits sound waves at a frequency of $!$5 \\ MHz$!$ for imaging a liver. The speed of sound in the liver tissue is $!$1540 \\ m/s$!$. If the ultrasound frequency is increased to $!$7.5 \\ MHz$!$, determine the new wavelength of the sound waves within the liver tissue.",
